According to official figures on balance of payments developments, China had a $217 billion deficit in tourism last year, equal to 44 percent of the entire Chinese surplus in trade in goods.
Thus, a small number of tourists strike a very painful blow to a country that is anxiously preventing capital outflows.
But the above factors are only one manifestation of a more general restraint against foreigners.
In many places in China, virtually no one has heard of immigrants.
