"If the NGO does not sign new rules of conduct, it will be hard for us to imagine that they could continue their operations," Interior Minister Marco Minniti said in an interview with Turin's La Stampa newspaper.
Minniti's warning came a day after Italian authorities seized the ship of German rescue organisation Jugend rettet on suspicion of human trafficking, significantly easing illegal immigration.
The rescue organisation, which operates in its first year, declined to comment on the matter because of allegations made by Italian prosecutor Ambrogia Cartosios.
"For us, it is and always will be the number one priority to save people's lives.... We are very sorry that we cannot currently operate in rescue zones," the organization said in a statement on social networks.
"We can only comment on all current charges after gathering all the information and evaluating the whole situation."
Italian authorities have been tracking the Iuventa organization's Jugend rettet since Oct.
