In the chalk period, giant Teropodi, carnivorous dinosaurs, moved on two legs.
Though the king of all dinosaurs - Tyrannosaurus rex - lived several million years after Borealopeltao, this armoured dinosaur may have been a favourite prey to its equally fearsome ancestors.
They include the Acrocanthosaurus, an 11.5-metre-long monster weighing over 6 tons.
